Source: libsapo-broker
Section: libs
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Daniel Ruoso <daniel.ruoso@segula.pt>
Build-Depends: cdbs, debhelper (>= 5), autotools-dev, libtool, autogen, autoconf, automake, libxml2-dev
Standards-Version: 3.7.2

Package: libsapo-broker0
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Client library for the SAPO Broker
 This library provides a high-level API for the SAPO
 Broker TCP agent. This is a synchronous API that
 manages the entire process of communicating with the
 broker.
 .
 This library also supports the TOPIC-AS-QUEUE 
 submission type. 

Package: libsapo-broker-dbg
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: libsapo-broker0 (= ${Source-Version}), ${misc:Depends}
Description: Client library for the SAPO Broker - Debug symbols
 This library provides a high-level API for the SAPO
 Broker TCP agent. This is a synchronous API that
 manages the entire process of communicating with the
 broker.
 .
 This library also supports the TOPIC-AS-QUEUE 
 submission type.
 .
 This package contains unstripped shared libraries. It is provided primarily
 to provide a backtrace with names in a debugger, this makes it somewhat
 easier to interpret core dumps. The libraries are installed in
 /usr/lib/debug and can be used by placing that directory in
 LD_LIBRARY_PATH.
 Most people will not need this package.

